Why use Python instead of the Console?
In real projects, scans are often automated.
Instead of manually clicking Run Scan every day in the GCP Console, you can write Python code and integrate it with an Airflow DAG.
For example:
Cloud Composer DAG
        │
        ▼
Dataflow finishes
        │
        ▼
PythonOperator
        │
        ▼
Dataplex Client
        │
        ▼
Run Profile Scan
        │
        ▼
Run Quality Scan
        │
        ▼
Check Results
        │
        ▼
Send Email if Scan Fails
This allows your data quality checks to run automatically as part of your data pipeline.
________________________________________
The Dataplex Python client is simply another way to use Dataplex.
You have two common ways to work with Dataplex:
1. Using the GCP Console (Manual)
•	Create Lake
•	Create Zone
•	Register Asset
•	Create Data Scan
•	Click Run Scan
2. Using Python (Programmatic)
•	Create Dataplex client
•	Create Data Scan
•	Run Data Scan
•	Read scan results
•	Integrate with Cloud Composer or other automation
Both methods use the same Dataplex service. The difference is only how you interact with it:
•	Console → Manual, point-and-click.
•	Python client → Automated, code-driven. This is the approach commonly used in production pipelines.

